Her use of email doesn't seem at all irresponsible to those of us who know, including Republicans in Congress who do the same thing though far less diligently. I'm not saying 'so what' or that it can't be done better by our government which actually invented email as a secure method of government communication, but absolutely zero problems have arisen out of her use of a separate e-mail server. This is an election year snipe hunt. BUT, of course this is also what we the people do right. We should question and accuse, point fingers and express our worst fears. And in Hillary Clinton's case she can handle it. That's why in little more than a week we shall address her as President Clinton. Please, keep it up long after the election.
